<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Use</h2>

  <p>
    For peppers in a cool basement, use a tray-sized heat mat directly under your trays during germination and early growth. Focus on even coverage and steady warmth rather than trying to push temperatures higher.
  </p>

  <p>
    Add a thermostat if your basement runs particularly cool, but keep the setup simple and consistent. Once seedlings are established, shift your focus to light and airflow rather than continued heating.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Warm the soil early, then let light and airflow take over.
  </p>
