<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Bottom Line</h2>

  <p>
    The best heat mat setup for peppers in a cool basement is one that provides steady, even bottom heat during germination and early growth without overcomplicating the system.
  </p>

  <p>
    For most gardeners, a simple tray-sized mat placed directly under the trays is enough to make a noticeable difference. The key is consistent warmth early on, followed by strong lighting and balanced conditions as the plants develop.
  </p>

